<br>
Same thing can be said by lots of other things, to name more books that have become movies. Stephen Kings Shawshank Redemption, The Green Mile, Stand By Me etc.. Those are remembered as movies by the majority i would assume. Even tho they are novellas written by Stephen King. <br>
<br>
So what do you think, will Lord of the Rings be remembered as a movie or a book? (50, 100, 150 years from now).<br>
<br>
Can you think of any other works of art that will be remembered as something else? And will we still be reading books for our own pleasure in the future?<br>
<br>
